&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF PSYCHIATRY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;LECTURER– CITIZENS ONLY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO. FM/PSY 1/2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; The successful applicant will be expected to: (i) teach both undergraduate and graduate Psychiatry courses (ii) engage in teaching clinical psychiatry at Sbrana Psychiatric Hospital, Princess Marina and other specified areas (iii) conduct research in his/her areas of expertise, (v) additionally, the successful candidate will be expected to undertake the following duties: research supervision, community service, research grant writing and resource mobilization, contribute towards departmental strategic plan development, and create relevant industry links for competency-based learning of the MMed residents nationally and or internationally (v) carry out any other duties assigned by the Head of Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; - The applicants should have; &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; at least a Bachelor of Medicine/Bachelor of Surgery or other recognized Medical Doctor qualification and a Master of Medicine in Psychiatry (MMed); &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; In addition, the applicant should be registered or registerable with the Botswana Health Professions Council (BHPC). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The following will be added advantages; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;(i)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;evidence of governance and social engagement; &lt;strong&gt;(ii) &lt;/strong&gt;experience of teaching at a university or comparable institution; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;engagement in research and grants management.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; The University offers competitive salaries and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to apply:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the university determine their suitability for the position.  They should provide current CV’s (including telephone and e-mail), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, and THREE (3) reference letters.  Applicants should inform their referees to:  (i) Quote the position applied for and (ii) submit their references directly to the address below:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Faculty of Medicine, Corner of Notwane and Mabuto Road, University of Botswana, Private Bag 00713 Gaborone, Botswana; or Email to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:nkangana@.ub.ac.%20bw"&gt;nkangana@.ub.ac. bw&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

